I knew it.

172
00:12:31.718 --> 00:12:33.898
He's lying.

173
00:12:34.518 --> 00:12:35.838
You brat!

174
00:12:35.838 --> 00:12:38.518
How many times do I have to
tell you not to scamper around?

175
00:12:38.888 --> 00:12:40.808
Sorry.

176
00:12:42.708 --> 00:12:43.818
Scamper, scamper.

177
00:12:43.978 --> 00:12:45.218
Scamper, scamper.

178
00:12:45.218 --> 00:12:47.368
Scamper away, little froggies.

179
00:12:47.368 --> 00:12:48.928
Scamper away together.

180
00:12:50.488 --> 00:12:51.508
Mori-kun?

181
00:12:51.508 --> 00:12:52.578
Could it be?

182
00:12:53.468 --> 00:12:55.968
Yes, indeed.

183
00:12:56.398 --> 00:12:58.808
I've figured out the truth behind this case.

184
00:13:03.288 --> 00:13:04.668
Allow me to be direct.

185
00:13:05.308 --> 00:13:11.428
The culprit in this murder is the man
who discovered the body, Yamanashi-san.

186
00:13:13.678 --> 00:13:17.938
Him? But what about the man wearing the cap?

187
00:13:18.148 --> 00:13:19.908
No such man exists.

188
00:13:20.338 --> 00:13:24.438
We were fooled by Yamanashi-san's lie.

189
00:13:27.208 --> 00:13:29.028
You're lying!

190
00:13:29.028 --> 00:13:30.388
What proof do you have?

191
00:13:30.388 --> 00:13:32.118
I really did see him.

192
00:13:32.428 --> 00:13:34.448
Allow me to explain.

193
00:13:35.028 --> 00:13:40.218
It's possible that this case couldn't have
been solved by anyone other than me,

194
00:13:40.218 --> 00:13:42.128
who arrived just after Yamanashi-san.

195
00:13:43.668 --> 00:13:47.758
In fact, one clue is
disappearing as we speak.

196
00:13:48.358 --> 00:13:49.798
A clue?

197
00:13:51.088 --> 00:13:54.448
In order to cover the sound
of Kusano-san's scream,

198
00:13:54.448 --> 00:13:58.538
you attacked him the moment he put
his hands inside the hand drier.

199
00:14:07.858 --> 00:14:11.358
Then you activated the hand drier once again

200
00:14:12.048 --> 00:14:15.868
so a third party would discover the body.

201
00:14:20.408 --> 00:14:24.268
However, something unexpected occurred.

202
00:14:26.288 --> 00:14:29.048
How could you?

203
00:14:34.208 --> 00:14:35.788
You'll pay for this!

204
00:14:48.028 --> 00:14:51.108
You believed the hand
drier hadn't drowned out

205
00:14:51.108 --> 00:14:54.468
the loud noises made during your scuffle,

206
00:14:58.678 --> 00:15:03.828
so you hastily changed your plan
and decided you'd discover the body.

207
00:15:07.588 --> 00:15:08.688
It's an emergency!

208
00:15:08.688 --> 00:15:11.088
Someone help!

209
00:15:13.838 --> 00:15:14.858
Conan-kun.

210
00:15:19.948 --> 00:15:21.008
What's the matter?

211
00:15:21.708 --> 00:15:24.868
Kusano was taking a while
to return, so I came here.

212
00:15:27.978 --> 00:15:29.528
Ran, call an ambulance!

213
00:15:29.528 --> 00:15:30.158
Okay.

214
00:15:30.158 --> 00:15:31.458
And the police.

215
00:15:31.458 --> 00:15:32.468
Got it.

216
00:15:33.608 --> 00:15:35.488
Damn. He's dead.

217
00:15:42.998 --> 00:15:45.878
Naturally, there's no man wearing a cap.

218
00:15:46.368 --> 00:15:49.998
It's a lie you made up to
confuse the investigation.

219
00:15:50.198 --> 00:15:51.898
That's a false accusation.

220
00:15:51.898 --> 00:15:54.948
How can you call someone
a liar without any proof?

221
00:15:54.948 --> 00:15:57.008
Do you have any proof?

222
00:15:57.008 --> 00:16:01.678
The first piece of evidence I mentioned
earlier is already disappearing.

223
00:16:02.098 --> 00:16:05.158
When I saw you in front of the bathroom,

224
00:16:05.158 --> 00:16:07.018
I felt as though something was off.

225
00:16:13.718 --> 00:16:16.308
The cuff of your pants was wet,

226
00:16:17.538 --> 00:16:22.158
